Scope:
  Exact cpp_int arithmetic checks the identity

    Q=-[e_2 wedge e_3]
       (wedge^2(A^(difference+half_power) B^half_power))
       (e_0 wedge Ae_0)

  against direct cyclic evolution, where A=2I-S-S^(-1),
  B=2I+S+S^(-1), and AB=2I-S^2-S^(-2).  The target range is
  difference>=2 and half_power>=2.  Nonnegativity in the displayed
  finite box is evidence only.  The exterior identity itself is exact.
  The program independently factors A^M B^r=HH^* with
  H=(I-S)^M(I+S)^r and checks the resulting Cauchy--Binet identity.
  The sign-conflict and intertwiner lines rule out the corresponding
  simple invariant-orthant and Gram-collapse ansatzes.  The positive
  Cauchy--Binet counters show that neither individual minors nor grouping
  them by cyclic separation or centre has the sign needed for a direct
  termwise proof.
